
[1]unitarian

   UNITA'RIAN, n. [L. unitus, unus.] One who denies the doctrine of the
   trinity, and ascribes divinity to God the Father only. The Arian and
   Socinian are both comprehended in the term Unitarian.

   UNITA'RIAN, a. Pertaining to Unitarians, or to the doctrine of the
   unity of the Godhead.
